Here are the public test cases for feature5_is_due:
{
    "description": "Decide whether a recurrence-rule schedule is due to fire, given a fixed 'current time' and a supplied 'last run' moment, and report when the following firing is expected. The schedule is due when an occurrence falls at or before the current time relative to the last-run moment. The result carries a due flag plus a 'next' value: when the schedule is due, 'next' is the number of seconds until the subsequent occurrence (or absent if none remain); when it is not due, 'next' is the seconds until the upcoming occurrence (or absent if the schedule is exhausted). A schedule whose start anchor lies in the future is not yet due but still reports the time until its first firing. A schedule limited to a single occurrence is due exactly once and reports no following occurrence; a schedule limited to two occurrences becomes not-due after each firing and reports no following occurrence once both are consumed.",
    "cases": [
        {
            "input": {
                "op": "is_due",
                "now": {
                    "year": 2020,
                    "month": 1,
                    "day": 1,
                    "hour": 0,
                    "minute": 0,
                    "second": 0
                },
                "rrule": {
                    "freq": "MINUTELY",
                    "dtstart": {
                        "year": 2020,
                        "month": 1,
                        "day": 1,
                        "hour": 0,
                        "minute": 0,
                        "second": 0
                    }
                },
                "last_run_at": {
                    "year": 1970,
                    "month": 1,
                    "day": 1
                }
            },
            "expected_output": "due=true\nnext=60.0\n"
        },
        {
            "input": {
                "op": "is_due",
                "now": {
                    "year": 2020,
                    "month": 1,
                    "day": 1,
                    "hour": 0,
                    "minute": 0,
                    "second": 0
                },
                "rrule": {
                    "freq": "MINUTELY",
                    "dtstart": {
                        "year": 2020,
                        "month": 1,
                        "day": 1,
                        "hour": 0,
                        "minute": 0,
                        "second": 0
                    },
                    "count": 1
                },
                "last_run_at": {
                    "year": 1970,
                    "month": 1,
                    "day": 1
                }
            },
            "expected_output": "due=true\nnext=none\n"
        }
    ]
}

