{
    "description": "Compute the remaining time until a recurrence-rule schedule's next firing, measured from a fixed 'current time' against a supplied 'last run' moment. The estimate is the gap between the current time and the next occurrence at or after the last-run moment. While the rule still has future occurrences the estimate is a positive number of seconds; once the schedule's occurrences are exhausted (e.g. its occurrence count has been used up) there is no next firing and the estimate is reported as absent. The current time, the rule's start anchor, and the last-run moment are all provided explicitly so the result is deterministic.",
